# Course Management Platform API Tests
# Use this file with REST Client extension or similar tools

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5000/api/health

### Register Admin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testadmin@example.com",
  "password": "admin123",
  "role": "admin"
}

### Login Admin
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@courseplatform.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login Student
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@student.com",
  "password": "student123"
}

### Get All Courses (Public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/courses

### Get Single Course (Public)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/courses/COURSE_ID_HERE

### Create Course (Admin only - replace TOKEN)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "title": "Advanced React Development",
  "description": "Learn advanced React patterns, hooks, and performance optimization techniques.",
  "category": "Programming",
  "thumbnail": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1633356122544-f134324a6cee?w=300&h=200&fit=crop"
}

### Enroll in Course (Student only - replace TOKEN and COURSE_ID)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "courseId": "COURSE_ID_HERE"
}

### Get My Enrollments (Student only)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/enrollments/my
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN_HERE

### Get Enrollment Status (Student only)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/enrollments/COURSE_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN_HERE

### Update Progress (Student only)
PUT http://localhost:5000/api/enrollments/COURSE_ID_HERE/progress
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_STUDENT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "completedModules": ["module1", "module2", "module3"]
}